{
  "model": "blog.post",
  "pk": 10,
  "fields": {
    "title": "Introduction to Django",
    "slug": "introduction-to-django",
    "author": 1,
    "body": "What is Django?\r\n\r\nDjango is a high-level Python web framework that enables developers to build secure and scalable web applications quickly. It follows the “batteries-included” philosophy, meaning it comes with many built-in features.\r\n\r\nKey Features\r\nRapid Development: Helps build applications faster with less code.\r\nSecurity: Protects against common threats like SQL injection and cross-site scripting.\r\nScalability: Suitable for both small projects and large-scale applications.\r\nORM (Object-Relational Mapping): Simplifies database interactions.\r\nWhy Use Django?\r\n\r\nDjango reduces development time by handling many common tasks such as authentication, routing, and database management. It allows developers to focus more on building unique features.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\n\r\nDjango is a powerful and beginner-friendly framework for web development, making it a popular choice for developers worldwide.",
    "status": "PB",
    "publish": "2026-03-25T07:11:24Z",
    "created": "2026-03-25T07:12:11.119Z",
    "updated": "2026-03-25T07:12:11.119Z"
  }
},
